  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "QA",
      "time": 60,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "05_qa_arithmetic_1_q1",
          "questionNumber": 1,
          "type": "MCQ",
          "question": "In an election between two candidates, the candidate who gets 30% of the votes polled is\ndefeated by 15,000 votes. The number of votes polled in favour of the winning candidate is",
          "options": [
            "11,250",
            "15,000",
            "26,250",
            "37,500"
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "3",
          "explanation": "3 Let total number of votes be x.\nThen, 30% of x + 15000 = 70% of x\n => 15000 = 0.4x\n => x = 37500\nThe required number = 70% of 37500\n= ∩é┤\n70 37500\n100 = 26250",
          "difficulty": "Medium",
          "year": null,
          "slot": null,
          "section": "QA",
          "topic": "Basics of percentage",
          "subtopic": "Basics of percentage",
          "sourceQuestionPdf": "05 QA Arithmetic-1 Q.pdf",
          "sourceSolutionPdf": "05 QA Arithmetic-1 Sol.pdf"
        },
        {
          "id": "05_qa_arithmetic_1_q2",
          "questionNumber": 2,
          "type": "MCQ",
          "question": "Out of the shirts produced in a factory, 15% are defective, while 20% of the rest are sold in\nthe domestic market. If the remaining 8840 shirts are left for export, then the number of\nshirts produced in the factory is",
          "options": [
            "13600",
            "13000",
            "13400",
            "14000"
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "2",
          "explanation": "2 Let total shirts produced = 100x\nDefective = 15x\nRest = 85x\nShirts sold in domestic market = 17x\nRemaining shirts = 68x\nSo, 68x = ∩Çá 8840\n => 100x = ∩Çá 13000.",
          "difficulty": "Medium",
          "year": null,
          "slot": null,
          "section": "QA",
          "topic": "Basics of percentage",
          "subtopic": "Basics of percentage",
          "sourceQuestionPdf": "05 QA Arithmetic-1 Q.pdf",
          "sourceSolutionPdf": "05 QA Arithmetic-1 Sol.pdf"
        },
        {
          "id": "05_qa_arithmetic_1_q3",
          "questionNumber": 3,
          "type": "TITA",
          "question": "A college has raised 75% of the amount it needs for a new building by receiving an average\ndonation of Rs. 600 from people already solicited. People already solicited represents 60%\nof people, the college will ask for donations. If college is to raise exactly the amount needed\nfor the new building, what should be the average donation (in Rs.) from remaining people to\nbe solicited?",
          "options": [],
          "correctAnswer": "300",
          "explanation": "Let x be the total number of people, college will ask for\ndonations.\n Therefore ∩Çá People already solicited = 0.6x\nAmount raised from the people solicited\n= 600 x 0.6x = 360x\nNow 360x constitutes 75% of the amount.\nHence, remaining 25% constitutes 120x\n Therefore Average donation from remaining people\n= =\n120x 300\n0.4x",
          "difficulty": "Medium",
          "year": null,
          "slot": null,
          "section": "QA",
          "topic": "Basics of percentage",
          "subtopic": "Basics of percentage",
          "sourceQuestionPdf": "05 QA Arithmetic-1 Q.pdf",
          "sourceSolutionPdf": "05 QA Arithmetic-1 Sol.pdf"
        },
        {
          "id": "05_qa_arithmetic_1_q4",
          "questionNumber": 4,
          "type": "MCQ",
          "question": "The income of Amala is 20% more than that of Bimala and 20% less than that of Kamala. If\nKamala's income goes down by 4% and Bimala's goes up by 10%, then the percentage by\nwhich Kamala's income would exceed Bimala's is nearest to",
          "options": [
            "29",
            "31",
            "28",
            "32"
